The ferry may suggest a need for patience, as it can take time to reach one's destination. It can also suggest a need for adaptability, as the journey may involve unexpected twists and turns. The ferry can represent a sense of adventure, excitement, or anticipation. It can also suggest a sense of uncertainty or risk.
